{"ts": "2026-06-07T11:32:56.709060+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Recommendation\n\nThe current `requirements.txt` (lines 1–6) lists packages without any version pins. Based on the team’s settled versions and the binding policy in PR #1, two lines need to change:\n\n| Line | Current value | Corrected pin | Reason |\n|------|--------------|---------------|--------|\n| 1 | `torch` | `torch>=2.4.0,<3.0.0` | Per the PR’s policy, torch bumps must use a **range** (not an exact pin). The lower bound is set to the agreed version `2.4.0` and the upper bound opens the patch range while staying on the 2.x major line. |\n| 4 | `torchtext` | `torchtext==0.18.0` | The team settled on `torchtext==0.18.0`; the range policy applies only to `torch`, so an exact pin is correct here. |\n\nThe remaining packages (`numpy`, `datasets`, `tqdm`, `matplotlib`) were not part of this bump and can stay unpinned (or be left as-is by whoever is driving the PR). After applying these two changes, the updated file would read:\n\n```\ntorch>=2.4.0,<3.0.0\nnumpy\ndatasets\ntorchtext==0.18.0\ntqdm\nmatplotlib\n```", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 352, "prompt_tokens": 6097, "total_tokens": 6449, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 47, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 6016}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 6016, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 81}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "ce24b4a5-d5bf-4b17-80ad-174eb0b60064", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea1db-6beb-7062-bcda-e4b82d3bfabb-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6097, "output_tokens": 352, "tot